s on marriage and family before and after emancipation. With an introduction that places the pension files in context and presents the themes of the book, and historical commentary interwoven throughout the excerpts of the interviews themselves, Elizabeth A. Regosin and Donald R. Shaffer effectively introduce the files and the treasures they contain to students and general readers, but also provide specialists with an indispensable research tool.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aAfrican American sailorsxPensions. 0aAfrican American soldiersxPensions. 0aAfrican AmericansxHistoryy1863-1877vSources. 0aAfrican AmericansxSocial conditionsy19th centuryvSources. 0aReconstruction (U.S. history, 1865-1877)vSources. 0aSlaveryzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th centuryvSources. 0aSlavesxEmancipationzUnited StatesvSources. 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh  aBureau.  aMining.  aPension.  aUS.  aVoices.  ablack.  acase.  aemancipation.  afiles.  afirst-hand.  afreedom.  ainvaluable.  amilitary.  aperspective.  aprovides.  aservice.  aslavery.1 aRegosin, Elizabeth A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShaffer, Donald R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814777343423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814777343/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17S